	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Sat, Jan 17th 12:58 PM 2004</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=148087><span id= >WarriorOne</span></a><br><span id=notbold>409 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.39]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>*blink* All classes are needed just much as the next one, granted some are more needed then others any day of the week (cleric, chanty, shammys are always in short supply on 7th hammer) But to say a ranger is always much more needed then an SK/Pally is just retarded, it depends on the situation, like say I know alot of higher end guilds who use SK's for tanks over warriors on SOME MOBS (i said SOME not ALL) because we can use Fearless disc, I also know alot of higher end mobs that use SK's over rangers as pullers because we can walk right up, chain cast aggro spells out the wazoo on a mob, and get CoH'd back, and not have to deal with gaurds, just let the raidmob warp back. All classes have theyre purpose and to say one is more needed then another is a retarded statement, some are more overpowered then other classes i'll agree on that, in the end game every class is needed. Thats why the classes were designed they way the were, Now I dont see why SoE is bringing us the &quot;Berserker class&quot; instead of working on classes that need it. </p>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
